<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[317,1271,436,1754]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
– After its description it has been known (
<bibRefCitation author="GRIFFITHS, G. C. D." box="[615,829,1531,1552]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="7 - 8" refId="ref22986" refString="GRIFFITHS, G. C. D. (1967 b) The Alysiinae (Hym. Braconidae) parasites of Agromyzidae (Diptera) III. The parasites of Paraphytomyza Enderlein, Phytagromyza Hendel and Phytomyza Fallen. Beitrage zur Entomologie 16 (7 - 8) (1966): 775 - 951." type="journal article" year="1967">GRIFFITHS 1967b: 678</bibRefCitation>
) for a long time only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1088,1180,1531,1552]" name="Germany" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Germany</collectingCountry>
; reported recently from 
<collectingCountry box="[451,537,1560,1581]" name="Hungary" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[546,610,1560,1581]" name="Serbia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[618,695,1560,1581]" name="Ukraine" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
and from the Asiatic 
<collectingCountry box="[899,963,1560,1581]" name="Russia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[974,1121,1560,1581]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Primorski Krai</collectingRegion>
, Chita Region). New to the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[521,583,1588,1609]" name="South Korea" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
